<div type="history" n="record">
<head>History of Recording</head>
<p>Both blocks copied in 1705 by Sherard (10101, 13v) and Picenini (10102, 24, and, from Tisser, 75 v); by Deering (11v-12, no. 38); by Fellows; ? perhaps by Bailie; by Loew; by Waddington. Left side fragment only recorded by Reichel (R.I.25v, mention); recorded by Gaudin (136); by the MAMA expedition; by the NYU expedition.</p>
